Functions

stderror <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))


rda2list <- function(file) {
  e <- new.env()
  load(file, envir = e)
  as.list(e)
}

loadRData <- function(fileName){
    load(fileName)
    get(ls()[ls() != "fileName"])
}

getmode <- function(v) {
   uniqv <- unique(v)
   uniqv[which.max(tabulate(match(v, uniqv)))]
}

predict.mics <- function(dat,model.list,model.name,breakpoint.l,breakpoint.h){
dat <- na.omit(dat)
a <- dat[dat$strain!="raw_NA",]

ifelse("ID" %in% colnames(a),a<-a, a <- transform(a, ID=as.numeric(interaction(strain, conc, cell_number, drop = T))))
preds.kp139 <- list()
pred.results <- list()
mics.a <- list()
mics.b <- list()
results <- list()
for (st in unique(a$strain)) {
test <- a[a$strain==st,]
cdc.mic <- unique(test$MIC)
mics.a[[st]] <- list()
mics.b[[st]] <- list()
tps <- c(2,4,6,8)
for (tp in tps) {
test.sub<-test[test$Time_Point<=tp,]
pred <- predict(model.list[[paste(model.name,tp,sep = "")]], test.sub, type="raw")
test.sub$pred <- formatC(pred$rf, digits = 1)

id.metrics <- list()
for (n in unique(test.sub$ID)) {
  m <- mean(as.numeric(test.sub$pred[test.sub$ID==n]))
  mo <- getmode(as.numeric(test.sub$pred[test.sub$ID==n]))
  id.metrics[[n]] <- data.frame(MIC.mean=m,MIC.mode=mo,ID=n,Strain=st)
}
id.metric.c <- rbindlist(id.metrics)

id.metric.c[id.metric.c$MIC.mode<=breakpoint.l, "pred"] <- "S"
id.metric.c[id.metric.c$MIC.mode>breakpoint.l & id.metric.c$MIC.mode<breakpoint.h, "pred"] <- "I"
id.metric.c[id.metric.c$MIC.mode>=breakpoint.h, "pred"] <- "R"
df <- data.frame(table(id.metric.c$pred)/sum(table(id.metric.c$pred))*100)
df$time <- tp
preds.kp139[[tp]] <- df 

id.metric.c$time <- tp
mics.a[[st]][[tp]] <- id.metric.c
}
preds.kp139.c <- rbindlist(preds.kp139)
mics.b[[st]] <- rbindlist(mics.a[[st]])
preds.kp139.c$strain <- st
pred.results[[st]] <- preds.kp139.c
}
pred.results.c <- rbindlist(pred.results)
mics <- rbindlist(mics.b)
results <- list(mics, pred.results.c)
return(results)
}

Generate bootstrapping groups in time point 1 and comparing the cluster sizes until time point 8

normalized.compressed <- j
ks <- c(1,3,5,7)
pb2 <- txtProgressBar(min = min(ks), max = max(ks), style = 3)
boots <- list()
for (z in ks) {
  setTxtProgressBar(pb2, z)
y <- normalized.compressed[normalized.compressed$Time_Point==1,]
iters <- 200
no.sampled <- z
pb <- txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = iters, style = 3)

boots[[z]] <- list()
for (i in unique(y$strain)) {
  boots[[z]][[i]] <- list()
  y.sub <- y[y$strain==i,]
  for (n in unique(y.sub$conc)) {
    y.s <- y.sub[y.sub$conc==n,]
    boots[[z]][[i]][[n]] <- list()
    print(paste("Sampling strain: ",i, " and concentration: ", n,sep = ""))  
    for (c in 1:iters) {
        setTxtProgressBar(pb, c)
        tmp <- y.s[sample(nrow(y.s),no.sampled,replace = TRUE),]
        tmp$group <- c
        tmp$no.samples <- z
        boots[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]] <- tmp
    }
  }
}

}
timepoints <- 8 
pb <- txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = timepoints, style = 3)
pb1 <- txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = iters, style = 3)

means.b <- list()
tmp.a <- list()
tmp.b <- list()
tmp.c <- list()
tmp.d <- list()
for (z in ks) {
  means.b[[z]] <- list()
  tmp.a[[z]] <- list()
  tmp.b[[z]] <- list()
  tmp.c[[z]] <- list()
  tmp.d[[z]] <- list()
  print(paste("No. of cells sampled: ", z, sep = ""))
  for (i in 1:timepoints) {
  print(paste("Time point: ", i, sep = ""))
  setTxtProgressBar(pb, i)
  y <- normalized.compressed[normalized.compressed$Time_Point==i,]
  means.b[[z]][[i]] <- list()
  tmp.a[[z]][[i]] <- list()
  tmp.b[[z]][[i]] <- list()
  for (n in unique(y$strain)) {
    y.s <- y[y$strain==n,]
    means.b[[z]][[i]][[n]] <- list()
    tmp.a[[z]][[i]][[n]] <- list()
    tmp.b[[z]][[i]][[n]] <- list()
    for (c in unique(y.s$conc)) {
      means.b[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]] <- list()
      tmp.a[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]] <- list()
      y.c <- y.s[y.s$conc==c,]
      print(paste("Sampling strain: ",n, " and concentration: ", c,sep = ""))
      for (p in 1:iters) {
        setTxtProgressBar(pb1, p)
        a <- boots[[z]][[n]][[c]][[p]]$cell.number
        tmp <- y.c[y.c$cell.number %in% a,]
        a.mean <- data.frame(t(colMeans(tmp[,c(1:20)])))
        a.mean$strain <- n
        a.mean$conc <- c
        a.mean$group <- p
        a.mean$time <- i
        a.mean$no.sampled <- z
        means.b[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]][[p]] <- a.mean
        
      }
      tmp.a[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]] <- rbindlist(means.b[[z]][[i]][[n]][[c]])
    }
    tmp.b[[z]][[i]][[n]] <- rbindlist(tmp.a[[z]][[i]][[n]])
  }
  tmp.c[[z]][[i]] <- rbindlist(tmp.b[[z]][[i]])
  }
  tmp.d[[z]] <- rbindlist(tmp.c[[z]])
}
means.b.compressed <- rbindlist(tmp.d)
means.b.compressed <- means.b.compressed[with(means.b.compressed, order(strain, conc, group, time))]
files <- list.files(folder, pattern = ".RData")
models <- Map(rda2list, file.path(folder, files))
names(models) <- tools::file_path_sans_ext(files)
accuracies <- list()

for (n in unique(names(models))) {
    m <- as.data.frame(as.array(summary(models[[n]]$rf$resample$Accuracy)))
    m$name <- n
    accuracies[[n]] <- m
}

mics <- list()
mics.e <- list()
for (e in 1:8) {
  tmp.sub <- tmp[[1]][tmp[[1]]$time==e,]
  for (i in unique(tmp.sub$Strain)) {
    mic.pred <- data.frame(strain=i,pred=getmode(tmp.sub$MIC.mode[tmp.sub$Strain==i]),mic=unique(y$MIC[y$strain==i]),time=e)    
    mics[[i]] <- mic.pred 
  }
  mics.e[[e]] <- rbindlist(mics)

tmp.mic.a <- list()
tmp.mic.b <- list()

  tmp.mic.a[[i]] <- list()
  for (j in c(2,4,6,8)) {
  tmp.i <- tmp[[1]][tmp[[1]]$Strain==i & tmp[[1]]$time==j,]
  tmp.i$exp.mic <- unique(y$MIC[y$strain==i])
  tmp.i$log2dil <- log2(tmp.i$exp.mic/tmp.i$MIC.mode)
  tmp.mic.a[[i]][[j]] <- tmp.i
  }
  tmp.mic.b[[i]] <- rbindlist(tmp.mic.a[[i]])
}

b <- ggplot(tmp.mic.c[tmp.mic.c$time==8,],aes(log2dil, fill=res)) + geom_histogram(aes(y = (..count..)/tapply(..count..,..PANEL..,sum)[..PANEL..])) + theme_classic() + geom_vline(xintercept = c(-1,1), lty=2) + ylim(0,1) + facet_grid(Strain~.) + xlab("") + ylab("")  + theme(strip.text.y = element_text(angle = 0, face = "bold", size = 15), axis.text = element_text(face = "bold", size = 10), legend.text = element_text(size=15), legend.title = element_text(size = 15)) + labs(fill="Resistance")
